{
  "_comment": "Pairwise ranking cases. For each pair, 'expected_higher' is 'a' or 'b'. We check that the importance score of the expected_higher event is actually higher. Cases probe known scoring issues.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "id": "mass_casualty_plateau",
      "description": "5000-fatality event vs 50-fatality event. Log-damping caps fatality_score at 14.0, so both score nearly the same on that component. The 5000-fatality event should still rank higher overall, but the margin will be tiny — revealing the cap problem.",
      "event_a": {
        "label": "Mass casualty attack kills 5000 in conflict zone",
        "entity_focus": ["Sudan", "RSF", "Khartoum"],
        "articles": [
          {"source": "Reuters", "source_domain": "reuters.com", "language": "en"},
          {"source": "BBC", "source_domain": "bbc.com", "language": "en"},
          {"source": "AP", "source_domain": "apnews.com", "language": "en"}
        ],
        "story_anchor_focus": ["strike", "attack"],
        "contradictions": [],
        "linked_structured_ids": ["ACLED-001"],
        "structured_meta": {"ACLED-001": {"fatalities": 5000}},
        "latest_observation": null
      },
      "event_b": {
        "label": "Clashes in border region kill 50",
        "entity_focus": ["Sudan", "RSF"],
        "articles": [
          {"source": "Reuters", "source_domain": "reuters.com", "language": "en"}
        ],
        "story_anchor_focus": ["attack"],
        "contradictions": [],
        "linked_structured_ids": ["ACLED-002"],
        "structured_meta": {"ACLED-002": {"fatalities": 50}},
        "latest_observation": null
      },
      "expected_higher": "a",
      "notes": "log1p(5000)*3.5 = 29.8, capped at 14.0. log1p(50)*3.5 = 13.7. The cap means 5000 deaths scores only 0.3 points more than 50 deaths on the fatality component. The difference comes from source_count (3 vs 1). Exposes how insensitive the score is to mass casualty scale."
    },
